comments.body:
@lovett so the conmon that was used in podman is in `/usr/lib/crio/bin/conmon` and the one you checked the version of is `/usr/lib/podman/bin/conmon`
two things: 
@saschagrunert : is the crio path still shipped with podman? or is that a remnant after upgrading?
@mheon: shouldn't podman look in the podman directory first?

ultimately @lovett, linking the podman one to the crio one will fix your problem. If you'd rather, you can also run `podman --conmon /usr/lib/podman/bin/conmon ...`
